ast=Turner|first=Chris|title=Snooker Awards|url=http://www.cajt.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Awards.html|work=cajt.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk|publisher=Chris Turner's Snooker Archive|accessdate=11 July 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724174749/http://www.cajt.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Awards.html|archivedate=24 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> The highest break of the qualifying stage was 141 made by [[Billy Kelly (snooker player)|Billy Kelly]].<ref name=\"Global Snooker\"/>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* 140, 112, 104, 103 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Steve James (snooker player)|Steve James]]\n* 125, 108, 101 {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Stephen Hendry]]\n* 124 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tony Knowles (snooker player)|Tony Knowles]]\n* 123, 118, 106, 104 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Steve Davis]]\n{{col-2}}\n* 119 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jimmy White]]\n* 114, 101 {{flagicon|WAL}} [[Terry Griffiths]]\n* 109, 105 {{flagicon|South Africa|1928}} [[Silvino Francisco]]\n* 102 {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Neal Foulds]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{World Snooker Championship}}\n{{Snooker season 1987/1988}}\n\n[[Category:World Snooker Championships|1988]]\n[[Category:1988 in snooker|World Championship]]\n[[Category:1988 in English sport|World Snooker Championship]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Sheffield]]\n[[Category:April 1988 sports events in the United Kingdom|World Snooker Championships]]\n[[Category:May 1988 sports events in the United Kingdom|World Snooker Championships]]\n", "name_user": "Rodney Baggins", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:location", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1988_World_Snooker_Championship"}
{"title_page": "Ajit Johnson", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Ajit Johnson\n| image = Ajit Johnson Nirmal.jpg\n| caption = Johnson at the [[Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology]] conference in 2015\n| birth_place = [[Chennai]], India\n| residence = [[Boston]], USA\n| workplaces = [[Harvard University]], [[Dana\u2013Farber Cancer Institute]]\n| alma_mater = {{plainlist|\n* [[University College London]]\n* [[University of Edinburgh]] }}\n| known_for = {{hlist|[[Computational Biology]]|[[Bioinformatics]]|[[Oncogenomics]]}}\n| website = {{url|http://www.ajitjohnson.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Ajit Johnson''' is a cancer geneticist. He has also campaigned to raise awareness on tech addiction and [[net neutrality]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/declancashin/talkin-bout-my-generation#.yhNNMQm2J|title=These Posters Perfectly Sum Up Twentysomethings' Addiction to the Internet|last1=Cashin|first1=Declan|publisher=BuzzFeed}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mckenna-bulkley/the-truth-about-thisgeneration_b_7056844.html|title=The Truth About #ThisGeneration|last1=Bulkley|first1=McKenna|publisher=www.huffingtonpost.com}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nBorn in [[Vellore]], Johnson graduated with a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[biotechnology]] at [[Karunya University]]. Johnson graduated from [[University College London]] in 2011 and worked at the [[Indian Institute of Science]]. He earned a Doctor of Philosophy in cancer [[genetics]] and [[genomics]] from the [[University of Edinburgh]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ethos.bl.uk/OrderDetails.do?uin=uk.bl.ethos.756770|title=British Library Thesis Collection|last=Nirmal|first=Ajit Johnson|date=2018-09-28|website=University of Edinburgh|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n=== Research ===\nJohnson and colleagues developed a cell based [[gene therapy]] for [[haemophilia]] patients at the [[National Cancer Centre Singapore]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sivalingam|first=Jaichandran|last2=Kenanov|first2=Dimitar|last3=Han|first3=Hao|last4=Nirmal|first4=Ajit Johnson|last5=Ng|first5=Wai Har|last6=Lee|first6=Sze Sing|last7=Masilamani|first7=Jeyakumar|last8=Phan|first8=Toan Thang|last9=Maurer-Stroh|first9=Sebastian|last10=Kon|first10=Oi Lian|date=2016-03-01|title=Multidimensional Genome-wide Analyses Show Accurate FVIII Integration by ZFN in Primary Human Cells|journal=Molecular Therapy|volume=24|issue=3|pages=607\u2013619|doi=10.1038/mt.2015.223|issn=1525-0016|pmc=4786920|pmid=26689265}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lee|first=Sze Sing|last2=Sivalingam|first2=Jaichandran|last3=Nirmal|first3=Ajit J.|last4=Ng|first4=Wai Har|last5=Kee|first5=Irene|last6=Song|first6=In Chin|last7=Kiong|first7=Chin Yong|last8=Gales|first8=Kristoffer A.|last9=Chua|first9=Frederic|last10=Pena|first10=Edgar M.|last11=Ogden|first11=Bryan E.|date=2018-07-01|title=Durable engraftment of genetically modified FVIII\u2010secreting autologous bone marrow stromal cells in the intramedullary microenvironment|journal=Journal of Cellular and Molecular Medicine|volume=22|issue=7|pages=3698\u20133702|doi=10.1111/jcmm.13648|issn=1582-1838|pmc=6010829|pmid=29682884}}</ref> Johnson developed ''ImSig'', a network-based computational framework that facilitates the characterization of immune [[Tumor-infiltrating lymphocytes|cells]] within the tumor microenvironment.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nirmal|first=Ajit J.|last2=Regan|first2=Tim|last3=Shih|first3=Barbara B.|last4=Hume|first4=David A.|last5=Sims|first5=Andrew H.|last6=Freeman|first6=Tom C.|date=2018-09-28|title=Immune Cell Gene Signatures for Profiling the Microenvironment of Solid Tumors|url=http://cancerimmunolres.aacrjournals.org/content/early/2018/10/22/2326-6066.CIR-18-0342|journal=Cancer Immunology Research|language=en|volume=6|issue=11|pages=1388\u20131400|doi=10.1158/2326-6066.CIR-18-0342|issn=2326-6066|pmid=30266715|doi-access=free}}</ref> Johnson's work involves multi-dimensional characterization (genetic, transcriptional, spatial and biophysical attributes) of the tumor ecosystem <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scholar.harvard.edu/ajitjohnson/home|title=Harvard Scholar Page|last=Nirmal|first=Ajit Johnson|date=|website=Harvard University|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and understanding the differences in molecular signature of immune cells <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Shih|first=Barbara B|last2=Nirmal|first2=Ajit J|last3=Headon|first3=Denis J|last4=Akbar|first4=Arne N|last5=Mabbott|first5=Neil A|last6=Freeman|first6=Tom C|date=2017-04-01|title=Derivation of marker gene signatures from human skin and their use in the interpretation of the transcriptional changes associated with dermatological disorders|journal=The Journal of Pathology|volume=241|issue=5|pages=600\u2013613|doi=10.1002/path.4864|issn=0022-3417|pmc=5363360|pmid=28008606}}</ref> across [[tumours]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* Official website: [http://www.ajitjohnson.com www.ajitjohnson.com]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Johnson, Ajit}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian biotechnologists]]\n[[Category:People from Vellore]]\n[[Category:Computational biologists]]\n[[Category:Cancer researchers]]\n[[Category:People from Harvard, Massachusetts]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Ajit Johnson\n| image = Ajit Johnson Nirmal.jpg\n| caption = Johnson at the [[Intelligent Systems for Molecular Biology]] conference in 2015\n| birth_place = [[Chennai]], India\n| residence = [[Boston]], USA\n| workplaces = [[Harvard University]], [[Dana\u2013Farber Cancer Institute]]\n| alma_mater = {{plainlist|\n* [[University College London]]\n* [[University of Edinburgh]] }}\n| known_for = {{hlist|[[Computational Biology]]|[[Bioinformatics]]|[[Oncogenomics]]}}\n| website = {{url|http://www.ajitjohnson.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Ajit Johnson''' is a can